Description: restore the _distribution/_patchlevel files configure.in reads
 bash 2.05's configure.in gets the version through
 esyscmd(cat _distribution) / esyscmd(cat _patchlevel), but the release tarball
 does not ship those two files -- they existed only in the maintainer's tree, and
 the shipped configure already had the values baked in.
 .
 We regenerate configure (the shipped one predates the toolchain), so the esyscmd
 calls run for real, come back empty, and BASHVERS/BASHPATCH end up blank.
 support/mkversion.sh then bails with a usage message, version.h is never
 written, and the build dies. Put the two files back.
 .
 Contents are version-derived, so there is one patch per baseline. 2.05a dropped
 this mechanism, hence 2.01..2.05 only.
Origin: vendor, shell-versions
Forwarded: not-needed

--- /dev/null
+++ _distribution
@@ -0,0 +1 @@
+2.05
--- /dev/null
+++ _patchlevel
@@ -0,0 +1 @@
+0
